The Chronicle Thandeka Moyo- Ndlovu, Chronicle Reporter FIFTEEN more people succumbed to Covid-19 while 321 others tested positive yesterday. The Ministry of Health and Child care says there are 108 hospitalized Covid-19 positive patients. <img class="wp-image-522837 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/12/coronavirus-cases-on-the-rise.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/12/coronavirus-cases-on-the-rise.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/12/coronavirus-cases-on-the-rise-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Of those admitted, five are in intensive care units. Of the 321 new cases, all are local cases and Harare province accounted for 91 of them. 1 985 tests were conducted countrywide. <img class="alignnone wp-image-494463 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/04/corona.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="379" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/04/corona.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/04/corona-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “We recorded 15 deaths and 321 new cases in the past 24 hours. As at 30 January 2021, Zimbabwe had 33 273 confirmed cases, including 25 361 recoveries and 1 193 deaths,” said the Ministry. – @thamamoe